The paper proposes a formalization of conceptual spaces, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI). The use of geometric representation and operations also suggests a connection to topics such as computational geometry and linear algebra, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the representation of correlations between different domains, which is a topic related to natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of fuzzy sets and the definition of operations for creating new concepts and measuring relations between them also suggests a connection to computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT).
